SECTION 37. IC 10-16-6-12, AS AMENDED BY P.L.238-2025,
SECTION 21, IS AMENDED TO READ AS FOLLOWS [EFFECTIVE
JULY 1, 2026]: Sec. 12. (a) A commissioned officer:
(1) who serves in the Indiana national guard for at least five (5)
years; or
(2) who becomes permanently disabled from performing the
officer's duties, irrespective of length of service;
may, upon retirement from the military service under conditions other
