is not entitled to receive any military pay or emolument from the state
during the time the officer remains on the national guard retired list
unless the officer is specifically assigned to duty on orders from the
governor. If the officer is assigned to duty on orders from the governor,
the officer is entitled only to the military pay and allowance provided
by law for officers of the rank to which appointed.
