this chapter with the board of commissioners in the county of residence
of the decedent described in subsection (a). The claim must include:
(1) the fact of the service, death, and discharge if discharged from
service before death; and
(2) that the body has been buried in a decent and respectable
manner in a cemetery or burial ground or that the body has been
cremated and the cremains have not been interred.
(c) The board of commissioners shall hear and determine the claim
like other claims and, if the facts averred are found to be true, shall
allow the claim in an amount set by ordinance. However, the amount
of the allowance may not be more than one thousand dollars ($1,000).
